.TH "splice_from_pipe" 9 "splice_from_pipe" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
splice_from_pipe \- splice data from a pipe to a file
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "ssize_t" splice_from_pipe
.BI "(struct pipe_inode_info *pipe "  ","
.BI "struct file *out "  ","
.BI "loff_t *ppos "  ","
.BI "size_t len "  ","
.BI "unsigned int flags "  ","
.BI "splice_actor *actor "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "pipe" 12
pipe to splice from
.IP "out" 12
file to splice to
.IP "ppos" 12
position in \fIout\fP
.IP "len" 12
how many bytes to splice
.IP "flags" 12
splice modifier flags
.IP "actor" 12
handler that splices the data
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
See __splice_from_pipe. This function locks the pipe inode,
otherwise it's identical to \fB__splice_from_pipe\fP.
